                <li>
                  Get Quotes: Obtain quotes for both repair and replacement,
                  including labor and parts.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Analyze Costs and Benefits: Compare the total cost of repair
                  versus replacement, factoring in potential energy savings,
                  improved efficiency, and possible tax incentives for new
                  equipment.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Consult with Stakeholders: Discuss the options with your
                  kitchen staff and financial advisors to get a comprehensive
                  view of the implications.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Make an Informed Decision: Based on the gathered information,
